==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semidiameter
<hw>Sem`i*di*am"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>Half of a diameter; a right line, or the length
of a right line, drawn from the center of a circle, a sphere, or other
curved figure, to its circumference or periphery; a radius.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semidiapason</ent>⟦br⟧
